verbose_text: We show here that HsSQM from the sulfo-ED cluster of H. seropedicaea can catalyze SQ mutarotation with a greater k cat / K M value than for the possible alternative substrate Glc-6-P, which is itself an important metabolite that feeds into the EMP and ED glycolytic pathways, as well as the pentose phosphate pathway.
evidence: HsSQM from the sulfo-ED cluster of H. seropedicaea can catalyze SQ mutarotation with a greater k cat
